snippet.textDisplay: ok so grey wins this hands down. besides the fact that ice magic has no effect on him in both the way that he trained to withstand it. but also the entire battle would just be the same as gray vs silver. greu could just eat all the ice esdeath throws at him. if you remember grey wasn't able to hurt silver until he used a cannon ball he found (not made of ice). So esdeaths powers are basically useless against him even her snow storm because grey just eats her soldiers before she can convert them. then when it comes to sword play, esdeath has the edge but what you forgot to take into consideration is that grey can control the black that is on his body, this gives him resistance where it's at meaning he could block esdeaths sword with just his body seeing that she most definitely doesn't have the sheer force that it would take to cut through it. let's also take into consideration grey's combat strategies, he's capable of creating a plan for an enemy he has no chance of beating just look at rufus, Mavis herself the fairy tactician calculated that he had basically no chance but because his pure brain power he best his opponent with only use each spell once. all in all grey outclasses esdeath if you take him after the series end, and even more so if you count his level in the 100 year quest.
